description: From fertility, with change of suffix after debilitate.

verbs.description: fertilitate (third-person singular simple present fertilitates, present participle fertilitating, simple past and past participle fertilitated)

entries.meaning: (rare, obsolete) To make fertile; to fertilize.
examples: a sweet rivolet playes wantonly in two streames through the Towne, fertilitating the Groves and Gardens
